description:
Electronic voting machines count about 87% of the votes cast in America today. But are they reliable? Are they safe from tampering? From a current congressional hearing to persistent media reports that suggest misuse of data and even outright fraud, concerns over the integrity of electronic voting are growing by the day. And if the voting process is not secure, neither is America\\\&amp;#039;s democracy. The timely, cautionary documentary HACKING DEMOCRACY exposes gaping holes in the security of America\\\&amp;#039;s electronic voting system.
